<subSubSection pageId="79" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="79.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,942,967]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1959" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[618,926,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis box="[618,777,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
Evans, 1959
</taxonomicName>
by having the median clypeal lobe quadrate with a median tooth on the apical margin; the circumocular suture present; the frons densely punctate; the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina followed by carinae and the posterior pronotal sulcus followed by a large foveae; the notaulus narrow; and the mesopleuron with the lower fovea closed, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[1183,1343,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis box="[1183,1343,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeus with the median lobe rounded, short, and with its apical margin truncate; the circumocular suture absent; the frons punctate; the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina and posterior pronotal sulcus without sculpture; the notaulus very narrow; and the mesopleuron with the lower fovea opened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
